# Fork-only PR policy

This clone uses a **fork workflow**. All publish/PR actions target the fork only.

## Remotes

- **`origin`** → `chuysmans/excalidraw` — all PRs and pushes go here.
- **`upstream`** → `excalidraw/excalidraw` — **read-only** (fetch, issues, reference code only).

## PR creation

- Always use: `gh pr create --repo chuysmans/excalidraw --base master`
- You may omit `--repo` only when `git remote get-url origin` confirms `chuysmans/excalidraw`.
- **Never** pass `--repo excalidraw/excalidraw`.
- **Never** open PRs against upstream or push to `upstream`.

## GitHub MCP

- When creating/updating/merging PRs via MCP, target **`chuysmans/excalidraw`** only.
- Reading upstream issues or PRs is allowed.

## Allowed upstream operations

- `git fetch upstream`
- `gh issue view`, `gh repo view`, read-only API calls against upstream
